From: Chris Mills <scm9985(-at-)tntech.edu>
Subject: Re: [T2] Leaking Windshield
 
">.. .water is STILL leaking through the windshield. How can I prevent
this? I
>didn't use any window sealer.. was I supposed to? I'm using that window
>gasket from West Coast Metric. 
 
NAPA and any glass shop can sell you urethane glass sealant in a caulking 
tube. $15 or so. Do not use silicone."

My .02-
I have used marine silicone ($5) with good results IE no leaking years
later. The question I have is why is it leaking? When you put the window
seal in was the metal all rotted? If using silicone, (and I am sure any
window sealant) make sure to clean the rubber and glass with alcohol to get
a good seal. 

Duncan
